            <li><strong>Cost:</strong> $8-$15/sq ft installed</li>
            <li><strong>DIY:</strong> Medium (great DIY project)</li>
            <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Medium (weed control)</li>
            <li><strong>Lifespan:</strong> 25-50 years</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 dark:text-neutral-200 mb-1">Loose Pea Gravel</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-neutral-550 dark:text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed text-pretty mb-3">
            The fastest, lowest-cost pathway option. Drains stormwater beautifully and offers a rustic, natural look. Requires a border edging frame to contain the stones, shifting gravel needs regular raking, and it cannot support thin-legged chairs or tables without a base layer.
